Name: 401-401 Great Northern Hwy, Middle Swan
Description: At peak times during school drop off and pick up the intersection (or lack of) cant address the necessary excessive traffic, forcing drivers to make risky decisions abut crossing and merging into a already very busy Road (Great Northern h/Way). In my case exiting Swan Christian Collage and trying to turn right to head south it is only through courteous actions of other who slow down and let people merge that prevents a complete standstill in traffic. A roundabout or Traffic lights are needed

Comment 333: Elizabeth: Very little chance to get a break in the traffic to cross the line of traffic. Volume of traffic limits accessibility to turn left or right. Wait times can be frustrating.
Comment 334: Jeanette: A large number of cars exiting from the school, trying to turn right onto Great Northern Highway.  They need to cross the busy road, which often has large road trains.  Vehicles travel along GNH at 80km/per hour making this a very dangerous road to try and enter.
Comment 336: Roundabout Rob: Since the reduction of the slower speed limit the traffic takes longer to clear a small roundabout is needed. You can use the school ground to build it. Slow speeds create more congestion which leads to frustration which leads to risk taking out of desperation and stress due to the 30 mins to get in and out of the school until we made it one way which i suggested years ago. Traffic lights create congestion. 111 deaths at lights in 10 years, 21 deaths at roundabouts. REMOVE LIGHTS SAFER FOR ALL.
Comment 423: Julie: Lights that operate for 1 hour during school drop off 7.4-8.45am and pick up 2.45-3.45pm would make a huge difference to traffic flow
Comment 501: M Lock: The lack of double lanes at this junction where the school traffic, trucks and cars merge makes for traffic congestion and backup to Oakover road. At school drop off and pick up times traffic is at a crawl. Also the new roundabout with only one lane for continuing to drive on Great Northern highway and the other dedicated lane to turn left only at Bishop Rd and Grt Nthrn Hwy intersection only exacerbates the traffic build up, as motorists all stay in right lane before the lights .
